There will be an information session on fishing issues in Cobourg Creek on March 28th.  https://www.facebook.com/ganaraska.fishway/photos/a.1581992018753670.1073741826.1581991978753674/1962136607405874/?type=3&theater  I fished the branch called Baltimore Creek up along Regional Road 45 working a summer job with the Conservation Authority back in '71, native Brookies ,Browns and Bows all in that branch then, caught my first decent Brown there, 17 inch  . Never been back.
going the same route as the ganny
I drive along there twice a month..I always wondered what the fishing was like....
